Home> About us> Entrepreneurship> Entrepreneur Of The Year> Ramzi HermizRamzi Hermiz Share 		Ramzi Hermiz 		2015 Road to Palm Springs 		Ramzi Hermiz is using technology and innovation to drive change in the automotive industry.	   		  		Shiloh Industries		President & Chief Executive Officer		Valley City, OH		Founded: 1950 		For more than 60 years, Shiloh Industries was a stalwart automotive supplier of stamping products and services. But Ramzi Hermiz had a different vision. In just three years as CEO, he has expanded Shiloh’s capabilities, acquiring and developing the most advanced technologies to reduce vehicle weight without compromising safety, strength, noise and vibration. 		Now the Valley City, OH-based company is the leading supplier of lightweighting solutions for automotive, commercial vehicle and industrial markets. They have a new logo, a new tagline – “Lightweighting without compromise” – and a new approach to market. 		Ramzi changed a company that got nearly half of its sales from Ford and Chrysler into a supplier serving a diverse group of automakers and specialty manufacturers, like Porche and Telsa. 		Ramzi more than doubled the number of employees and hired people with global experience. In turn, he created an environment that fosters problem-solving and idea-generation. Instead of just processing orders, they give customers choices that include mixes of metals and manufacturing options. 		Within three months of his arrival in 2012, Ramzi spearheaded Shiloh’s first acquisition since 2000. He’s since led five strategic acquisitions that leveraged key customer relationships around the world and expanded Shiloh’s global footprint in the US, Mexico, Poland, Sweden and China.	 














